.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH rom-weaver-bundle-create 1  "rom-weaver-bundle-create "
.SH NAME
rom\-weaver\-bundle\-create \- Build, validate, and write a rom\-weaver\-bundle.json bundle from local ROM/patch files
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrom\-weaver bundle create\fR [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-rom\fR] [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-rom\-url\fR] [\fB\-\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-rom\-name\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-name\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-description\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-label\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-optional\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-source\-url\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-header\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-basis\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-input\-check\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-output\-check\fR] [\fB\-\-output\-check\fR] [\fB\-\-output\-name\fR] [\fB\-\-output\-header\fR] <\fB\-\-output\fR> [\fB\-\-bundle\fR] [\fB\-\-bundle\-rom\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-bundle\-rom\fR] [\fB\-\-checksum\fR] [\fB\-\-threads\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Build, validate, and write a rom\-weaver\-bundle.json bundle from local ROM/patch files.
.PP
ROM checks are computed from the actual file (crc32/md5/sha1 by default). Per\-patch metadata flags (\-\-patch\-name, \-\-patch\-description, \-\-patch\-label, \-\-patch\-optional, \-\-patch\-source\-url, and \-\-patch\-header) bind to the most recent preceding \-\-patch. \-\-output accepts rom\-weaver\-bundle.json, rom\-weaver\-bundle.json.gz, or rom\-weaver\-bundle.json.zst; \-\-bundle additionally packs the bundle plus the local sources into one archive whose path entries reference the archived names.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit progress and terminal status as JSON lines
.TP
\fB\-\-rom\fR \fI<ROM>\fR
Local ROM file; its checksums/size become the bundle\*(Aqs rom checks
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR
Force running progress events on
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR
Disable running progress events
.TP
\fB\-\-rom\-url\fR \fI<ROM_URL>\fR
Emitted rom download url (combined with \-\-rom the local file still supplies checks; alone it emits a url\-only rom entry)
.TP
\fB\-\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs (also enabled by ROM_WEAVER_LOG or RUST_LOG)
.TP
\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs from dependencies (for example nod)
.TP
\fB\-\-rom\-name\fR \fI<ROM_NAME>\fR
Display/output\-naming file name for the rom entry
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\fR \fI<PATCH>\fR
Patch file to include, in apply order; repeat \-\-patch for each entry. \-\-patch\-name, \-\-patch\-description, \-\-patch\-label, \-\-patch\-optional, \-\-patch\-source\-url, and \-\-patch\-header bind to the preceding \-\-patch
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-name\fR \fI<PATCH_NAME>\fR
Display name for the preceding \-\-patch
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-description\fR \fI<PATCH_DESCRIPTION>\fR
Description for the preceding \-\-patch
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-label\fR \fI<PATCH_LABEL>\fR
Free\-form maturity or status label for the preceding \-\-patch
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-optional\fR \fI<PATCH_OPTIONAL>\fR
Set whether the preceding \-\-patch is optional; optional patches are deselected by default
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
true
.IP \(bu 2
false
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-source\-url\fR \fI<PATCH_SOURCE_URL>\fR
Emitted url source for the preceding \-\-patch (the local file is still read for the bundle)
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-header\fR \fI<PATCH_HEADER>\fR
Header handling mode for the preceding \-\-patch
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
keep
.IP \(bu 2
strip
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-basis\fR \fI<PATCH_BASIS>\fR
What the preceding \-\-patch\*(Aqs input checks were authored against: base (the bundle\*(Aqs rom) or previous (the prior patch\*(Aqs output, the default); auto omits the field for inference
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
base
.IP \(bu 2
previous
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-input\-check\fR \fI<PATCH_INPUT_CHECK>\fR
Expected pre\-apply ROM checksum for the preceding \-\-patch (algo=hex; repeatable and comma\-separable); emitted as inputChecks only when it differs from the rom checks. On the wasm path this is index\-aligned with \-\-patch (one comma\-separated value per entry, empty for none)
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-output\-check\fR \fI<PATCH_OUTPUT_CHECK>\fR
Expected post\-apply ROM checksum for the preceding \-\-patch (algo=hex; repeatable and comma\-separable); emitted as outputChecks only when it differs from the final output checks
.TP
\fB\-\-output\-check\fR \fI<OUTPUT_CHECK>\fR
Expected checksum of the final output once the full patch chain is applied (algo=hex; repeatable and comma\-separable); emitted as output.checks
.TP
\fB\-\-output\-name\fR \fI<OUTPUT_NAME>\fR
Default output file name the bundle suggests
.TP
\fB\-\-output\-header\fR \fI<OUTPUT_HEADER>\fR
Default header handling mode for the final bundle output
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
keep
.IP \(bu 2
strip
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR
Where to write the bundle: rom\-weaver\-bundle.json, or rom\-weaver\-bundle.json.gz / rom\-weaver\-bundle.json.zst for a compressed one
.TP
\fB\-\-bundle\fR \fI<BUNDLE>\fR
Also bundle the bundle plus the local rom/patch files into this archive (creatable formats only, for example .zip); bundle path entries then reference the archived names
.TP
\fB\-\-bundle\-rom\fR \fI<BUNDLE_ROM>\fR
ROM payload to package in \-\-bundle while \-\-rom supplies its checks and metadata
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-bundle\-rom\fR
Don\*(Aqt distribute the local \-\-rom: leave it out of \-\-bundle and emit its bundle entry with checks only (the applying user supplies the ROM)
.TP
\fB\-\-checksum\fR \fI<CHECKSUM>\fR
Checksum algorithm(s) for rom checks (repeatable; default crc32, md5, sha1)
.TP
\fB\-\-threads\fR \fI<auto|N>\fR [default: auto]
Thread budget: auto or a positive integer
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
